<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Beginner_BuildMode_BuyPlaceObjects" s="313994">
  <T n="name">0x5A97CFB5<!--String: "Buying & Placing Objects"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_BuyingAndPlacingObjects_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a554e7edcd4030ed</T>
      <T n="text">0x641F3D51<!--String: "The <b><font color='#199C2C'>Objects</font></b> in your house help your Sims to manage their Needs and Emotions, improving their Skills, and socializing with other Sims.\n\nWhen you <b><font color='#199C2C'>buy</font></b> new Objects, it’s important to keep your Sim’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>needs</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Household funds</font></b> (how much money they have) in mind. \n\nOr use a <b><font color='#199C2C'>money cheat</font></b>, more on that in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Cheats Lesson</font></b>!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_BuyingAndPlacingObjects_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a554e7edcd4030ee</T>
      <T n="text">0x77654425<!--String: "You can browse the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Object Catalog</font></b> by <b><font color='#199C2C'>Room</font></b> or <b><font color='#199C2C'>Function</font></b>. It’s a good idea to familiarize yourself with where Objects are located in the Catalog. Don’t forget to scroll!\n\nYou can also <b><font color='#199C2C'>search</font></b> for types of Objects or individual Object names."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_BuyingAndPlacingObjects_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a554e7edcd4030ef</T>
      <T n="text">0x18B70FA<!--String: "To <b><font color='#199C2C'>buy</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>place</font></b> an item, simply select it from the Catalog, move the cursor to where you want to place it, and click! The Object’s <b><font color='#199C2C'>footprint</font></b> must be <b><font color='#199C2C'>green</font></b>, which means there is enough space.\n\nTo <b><font color='#199C2C'>rotate</font></b> a held Object, click the right mouse button, [CTRL + RMB] will rotate in the opposite direction. \n\nYou can also select an already bought Object to move and rotate it, or sell it by pressing the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Sell button</font></b>."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\BuildMode\BuildMode_Eyedropper_1.png" n="image">2f7d0004:00000000:bf74da8b29b03fe0</T>
      <T n="text">0xFD0F1ED6<!--String: "The <b><font color='#199C2C'>Eyedropper</font></b> is a very useful tool for <b><font color='#199C2C'>buying a copy</font></b> of something you already own, such as adding more chairs to a table! \n\nSimply select the Eyedropper from the menu at the top of the screen, select an Object in your house, and place the new copy.\n\nYou can also use the Eyedropper as a <b><font color='#199C2C'>shortcut</font></b> to a specific <b><font color='#199C2C'>Catalog</font></b> category (for example, selecting a bed to open the Beds category)."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
